'''Shuckin' and Jivin' ''' is a term popular among [[African Americans]] of North America primarily.  It loosely means "to sit around in a group, outdoing each other with lies and exaggerations."

The origin of the term is unknown, however it most likely originated during the US [[Slavery]] period, when African Americans were forced to perform menial labor. To entertain themselves, they probably played games similar to [[playing the dozens]] or telling tall tales while performing work, such as [[wiktionary:shuck|shucking corn]]. 

Nowadays Shuckin' and Jivin' can also refer to a group of [[busybody|busybodies]] or other foolish people. For example, "Those guys are always down by the store, shuckin' and jivin' about the new family's business."

